The paper deals with the Index Coding with Side Information (ICSI) problem, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are subfields of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of finding the min-rank of a digraph is related to network coding and communication networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the complexity of decision problems, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and the use of linear codes, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
